server creation -nodejs + Express

Basic commands
--------------

1)Creating package.json -npm init
2)Creating node modules -npm i express (insatall express)
3)install nodemon -npm install -g nodemon
4)run - nodemon index.js
5)Install Mongose-npm i mongoose


Basic steps
------------

1)Creating a folder (Bankserver)
2)Creatin package.json file
3)install express
4)import express inside the index.js file
5)Create an app using express
6)Setip the port number
7)resolving htp request 

8)HTTP Response code
    1xx-information
    2xx-succesfull
    3xx-redirection
    4xx-client error
    5xx-server error

9)JWT Token
install JWT token -npm i jsonwebtoken
To generate token -sign()


10) Middleware
It comes in the middleware of the request and the response cycle of the nodejs execution process

        req,res,next

        1)applicaion specific middleware  -For entire application
        2)router specific middleware  -FOr token verificatoin-verify()
        

12)Database integration
    1)Install Mongose-npm i mongoose

13)Asynchrouns function resolving-promise

 1)Resolve State- .then()
 2)Reject state-catch()

14)CROS -cross origin resourse sharing 

    install cors -nom i cors

    port 4200 (angular) -----request---->3000(node)(reactive)



15)Asynchrounts call -RxJs-(reactive extension for javascript)

js-promise
ts-RxJs(library)

 1)Observable
     a)resolved -Subscribe()
     b)reject-catch()